    <h1>Security</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 id=3D"Security-Levelsofsecurity">Levels of security</h1>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Security defined in RAS
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Authentication
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Password which is salted and hashed in the database</li>
<li>Two factor authentication</li>
<li>User receives authentication token which expires after a programmable p=
eriod</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Company level security&nbsp;</li>
<li>Feature level security</li>
<li>Item level security</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Configuration
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Specific user accounts for processes</li>
<li>File security</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Protocols
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>HTTPS</li>
<li>FTPS</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"Security-Typesofsecurity">Types of security</h1>
<p>In RAS we have three types of authorization constraints.&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Security-Authentication">Authentication</h2>
<p>User accounts are invite only. Only an administrator can send out an inv=
itation or can manually create a new user account.</p>
<p>User accounts are RAS specific, they are not linked to other user stores=
 such as domain level authentication or external accounts.</p>
<p>Every user has to specify a password with which they identify themselves=
. They also have the option to enable two factor authentication.</p>
<p>User's with the administrator permission will get a nag screen every hou=
r if they don't have 2FA enabled on their account.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Security-Twofactorauthentication(2FA)">Two factor authentication =
(2FA)</h3>
<p>For each user, a unique secret is stored in the database. When 2FA is se=
tup, this secret is embedded inside a QR code which the user has to scan wi=
th their preferred authenticator app.</p>
<p>The algorithm in use is TOTP, which generates a unique numeric code of s=
ix digits every 30 seconds. Upon login the system will ask the user to ente=
r his code valid at that time.</p>
<p>Note that the clock on both devices need to be more or less in sync with=
 reality for this to work.</p>
<p>For more information on TOTP see&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time-based_One-time_Password_algorithm" rel=
=3D"nofollow">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time-based_One-time_Password_al=
gorithm</a></p>
<h2 id=3D"Security-Companylevelsecurity">Company level security</h2>
<p>Every user can only be assigned to one company. Each company can have ma=
ny assets.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image confluence-external-resour=
ce" height=3D"48" width=3D"468" src=3D"1836e5262986874227444c85f045e464" da=
ta-image-src=3D"/wiki/download/attachments/83755549/Untitled%20Diagram.draw=
io.png?api=3Dv2" loading=3D"lazy"></span></p>
<p>As this would expose all the data of the company to every user in the co=
mpany we have to define additional levels of security such as feature level=
 and item level security.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Security-Featurelevelsecurity">Feature level security</h2>
<p>This level of security focuses on the permissions we assign to a user wh=
ich allow them access to features of the system.</p>
<p>We have identified the following list of permissions:</p>
<ul>
<li><label><strong>view_filters</strong>: Is able to see filters that belon=
g to&nbsp;<label>or are shared with the user</label></label></li>
<li><label><strong>edit_filters</strong>: <label><label><em>Requires: view_=
filters.</em>&nbsp;</label></label>Is able to create and edit filters. This=
 permission gives the user access to all the data of the company it belongs=
 to.</label></li>
<li><label><strong>view_dashboards</strong>: Is able to view dashboards tha=
t belong to him or are shared with the user.</label></li>
<li><label><strong>edit_dashboards</strong><label>: <em>Requires: view_dash=
boards.</em> Is able to create and edit dashboards, which contain data base=
d on filters</label></label></li>
<li><label><strong>view_reports</strong><label>:&nbsp;<label>Is able to vie=
w reports that belong to him or are shared with the user.</label></label></=
label></li>
<li><label><strong>edit_reports</strong><label>:&nbsp;<label><label><em>Req=
uires: view_reports.</em> Is able to create and edit reports, which contain=
 data based on filters</label></label></label></label></li>
<li><label><strong>edit_scheduled_tasks</strong><label>: Is able to create =
and edit scheduled tasks</label></label></li>
<li><label><strong>permission_delegation</strong><label>: Not implemented y=
et (idea is to allow a company administrator to grant permissions to compan=
y users)</label></label></li>
<li><label><strong>view_data_analysis_definition</strong><label>: Is able t=
o list all data analysis definitions</label></label></li>
<li><label><strong>edit_data_analysis_definition</strong><label>: Is able t=
o create, edit and enable/disable data analysis definitions</label></label>=
</li>
<li><label><strong>administrator</strong><label>: Is able to see the admini=
stration section which allows a user to:&nbsp;</label></label>
<ul>
<li>change messaging quota settings</li>
<li>manage users
<ul>
<li>manage permissions</li>
<li>create or send invitation</li>
<li>disable 2FA per user</li>
<li>send password reset email</li>
<li>impersonate</li>
<li>send notification</li>
</ul></li>
<li>manage all companies
<ul>
<li>create</li>
</ul></li>
<li>manage all assets
<ul>
<li>set associated companies</li>
<li>change image</li>
<li>change upload password</li>
</ul></li>
<li>manage asset types</li>
<li>monitor inbound handlers</li>
<li>view application logs</li>
<li>view current cache and their memory usage (not values, only keys)</li>
<li>view email + notification quotum for each user and system wide</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>These permissions can be assigned to users by the administrator of the s=
ystem, which is any user that has the administrator permission.&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Security-Itemlevelsecurity">Item level security</h2>
<p>This level of security defines who can access which specific object (das=
hboard, filter, etc)</p>
<p>Users can create dashboards, filters, reports, data analysis definitions=
 and scheduled tasks. Each of these objects are assigned an owner upon crea=
tion. This is the user that has created the object.</p>
<p>The system also allows users to share the items they've made with other =
users, this can be done in collaboration (both can edit) or as read-only. T=
his is called <strong><a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/RASNEX/pages/83755379/6.1.1+D=
ata+Sharing" data-linked-resource-id=3D"83755379" data-linked-resource-vers=
ion=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">Item sharing</a></strong>.</p>
<p>Another possibility is that a user creates an object for someone else. T=
hey can then create the object and transfer it to another user. This is cal=
led&nbsp;<strong><a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/RASNEX/pages/83755507/6.1.3+Transf=
erring+Ownership" data-linked-resource-id=3D"83755507" data-linked-resource=
-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">Ownership t<strong>ransfe=
r</strong></a></strong>.</p>
<h1 id=3D"Security-Implementationsecurityofhardwareandsoftware">Implementat=
ion security of hardware and software</h1>
<p>Applications and websites are hacked every day. As we're dealing with hi=
ghly sensitive information we have thought about security at every step of =
the implementation.</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Every website runs under it's own application pool identity</li>
<li>File permissions are kept to the absolute minimum required for each app=
lication</li>
<li>Every process is running under it's own specific user</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"Security-Assetdataauthenticity">Asset data authenticity</h2>
<p>To ensure data being sent from the devices to RAS is authentic, the syst=
em generates a unique login and password for each asset which should be pro=
grammed into the asset. Only administrators can change this password.</p>
<p>The system encourages the use of secure communication protocols such as =
HTTPS or FTPS. However to facilitate older devices the system also supports=
 FTP.</p>
<p><br></p>
    </div>
